    {
      "name": "Complete Test Workflow",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "WORKFLOW: Complete Authentication & Testing Flow",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:8080/api/v1/products",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "8080",
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "products"
              ]
            },
            "description": "COMPLETE TEST WORKFLOW:\n\n1. Run: \"1. Register New User (Valid)\" - Create testuser1 account\n2. Run: \"5. Login (Valid Credentials)\" - Login with testuser1\n   - Postman automatically stores JSESSIONID cookie\n3. Run: \"Products - Public Access\" requests - Should work without login\n4. Create an ADMIN user:\n   - Register with role: \"ADMIN\"\n   - Login with that user\n5. Run: \"Products - Admin Only\" requests - Should work with ADMIN role\n6. Run: \"6. Logout\" - Logout and clear session\n7. Try \"4. Create Product (Without Authentication)\" - Should get 401 error\n\nExpected Results:\n- Public endpoints work without authentication\n- Protected endpoints require valid session (JSESSIONID cookie)\n- Admin endpoints require ADMIN role\n- Validation errors return detailed error messages\n- After logout, protected endpoints return 401 Unauthorized"
          },
          "response": []
        }
